	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Maiduguri – At least one person was reported dead following two
bomb blasts at the University of Maiduguri in northern Nigeria on Thursday
night. According to Afripost Nigeria, the first explosion went off
at about 22:50 around the Faculty of Veterinary Medicine. The second one went off at mid night at a women’s hostel,
killing a campus security guard, a report by Bloomberg said. More to follow... 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  